>NAME

rewinddir - rewind directory reader

>SYNOPSIS

	#include <dirent.h>
	
	void rewinddir(DIR *'dirp');

>DESCRIPTION

This function resets the directory reader 'dirp', previously opened by [opendir.2], back to the first entry. A subsequent call to [readdir.2] will therefore return the first entry.

>ERRORS

This function reports no errors.

